            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Accounts payable arise from supplier invoices already received and entered, while accrued liabilities are estimates for goods or services consumed where no invoice has arrived yet. Payables carry a bill number, due date and vendor ledger; accruals are journal estimates reversed next period. Both sit under current liabilities, with accruals shown as other current liabilities."
          }
